                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_108012">Daventry</placeName> and <placeName key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName>, The Symond Holding.

Indenture by which <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Saloman</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName>
                        </persName> grants to <persName nymRef="Symond">
                           <forename>Matilda</forename> wife of <persName>
                              <forename>Robert</forename> 
                              <surname>Symond</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                              </placeName>
                           </persName>
                        </persName> and <persName nymRef="Symond">
                           <forename>Matilda</forename> their daughter</persName>, one acre 2 roods of arable land in the South field of <placeName key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName>, viz. one acre lying together at ‘<placeName type="minor">le Crosweye</placeName>’ over ’<placeName type="minor">le Brodebottes</placeName>’ by the said Matilda’s land, one rood under <placeName type="minor">Stepenhul</placeName> by the said Matilda’s land, one rood into <placeName type="minor">Westegrovesithe</placeName> by the lord of D<supplied>aventry</supplied>’s land, from Michaelmas 17 Ed. III. for 12 years. [<hi rend="italic">Rent not given.</hi>] 
   Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Wylymet</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </placeName>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> de <surname>aula</surname>
                        </persName> of the same, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Werrour</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName>
                        </persName>. 
   <origDate when="1343-09-29">
                           <supplied>29 Sept. 1343.</supplied>
                        </origDate>
                     </p>
